4.1 Binary Input/Output

* Binary I/O means reading/writing raw binary formats or primitives in a consistent binary layout.

➡ DataOutputStream / DataInputStream let you write/read Java primitive values in a
  portable binary form (writeInt, writeDouble, readUTF, etc.).

➡ Use BufferedOutputStream/BufferedInputStream around them for performance.

  Example:

  try (DataOutputStream dos = new DataOutputStream(
           new BufferedOutputStream(new FileOutputStream("data.bin")))) {
      dos.writeInt(2025);
      dos.writeDouble(3.14);
      dos.writeUTF("hello");
  }

  try (DataInputStream dis = new DataInputStream(
           new BufferedInputStream(new FileInputStream("data.bin")))) {
      int year = dis.readInt();
      double pi = dis.readDouble();
      String s = dis.readUTF();
  }
